1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
SmartMaint — L.C PROD. A GMAO for a Moroccan edible-oil plant.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,500
Real-time sync across 27 tables. Offline French voice dictation.

3
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:12,500
Arabic RTL for the shop floor. Windows installer with auto-update.

4
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,000
Full-stack Next.js and Supabase. Let me show you.

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
The admin cockpit — every KPI live-computed from intervention history.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,500
Every machine has a QR code, a criticality score, and a full audit trail.

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:30,500
Interventions are Kanban — click and drag to reassign or close.

8
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:37,500
All 27 tables sync in real time — ~180 ms across all logged-in sessions.

9
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:51,000
The technician view is mobile-friendly, meant for a tablet on the shop floor.

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Every text field has a microphone — Whisper-small, 240 MB, running in the browser.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:03,500
So the technician can dictate their report in French even offline.

12
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:09,000
Photos tag automatically as "before" or "after".

13
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:15,000
And a QR scanner jumps straight to the machine card. Instant identification.

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,000
The operator interface is Arabic, right-to-left, kiosk-first.

15
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,500
Giant tactile buttons for panic, quality defect, and requesting EPI.

16
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:37,000
No training required — an operator filed their first report in under 20 s.

17
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Every request lands instantly on the admin's screen.

18
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:56,000
And the piece I'm most proud of technically — auto-update, on Windows.

19
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:02,500
Getting this to work was a two-week deep dive.

20
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:09,000
The launcher wraps Node in a Windows Job Object with KILL_ON_JOB_CLOSE.

21
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:14,500
That normally kills every child process when the launcher exits —

22
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:19,500
so my restart script kept dying with its parent.

23
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:25,000
Fix: ask WMI to spawn PowerShell — the child ends up outside the Job.

24
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:30,000
55,000 lines of TypeScript. 80 user stories. 15 sprints.

25
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,500
Three roles, three languages, one platform.

26
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:40,000
Full source, architecture doc, and blog write-ups are on GitHub.

27
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Live demo in the description. My LinkedIn is on screen.

28
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:52,000
If you're hiring a full-stack engineer for industrial software, DM me.

29
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Thanks for watching.
